    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The current military posture and activity patterns suggest a focus on transport and patrol missions, with a significant presence of US Air Force and US Navy assets. The deployment of the USS San Antonio (LPD-17) to U.S. Southern Command and its recent return to port indicate a strong emphasis on amphibious operations. The presence of intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (ISR) aircraft, such as the one with hex code adfd6d, suggests a continued focus on gathering intelligence and conducting reconnaissance operations. The overall assessment is that the US military is maintaining a robust presence and posture, with a focus on supporting ongoing operations and maintaining readiness for potential future conflicts.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
